    "heading_text": "Tags",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/path-operation-configuration/#tags",
    "chunk_index": 0,
    "chunk_text": "Tags. You can add tags to your path operation , pass the parameter tags with a list of str (commonly just one str ): They will be added to the OpenAPI schema and used by the automatic documentation interfaces: Tags with Enums. If you have a big application, you might end up accumulating several tags , and you would want to make sure you always use the same tag for related path operations . In these cases, it could make sense to store the tags in an Enum . FastAPI supports that the same way as with plain strings:",
